Europe-wide survey of 19,000 people revealed that the more a country paid to the unemployed or sick the more likely its residents were to want a job . 
  In Norway, which pays the highest benefits in Europe, almost 80% of people wanted a job  . 
  In Estonia, one of the least generous countries, only 40% wanted to work . 
  People who are hungry are more inclined to support the welfare state policies that help the poor . 
 